4.36. А body of mass $m$ was suspended by a non-stretched spring, and then set free without push. The stiffness of the spring is $\varkappa$. Neglecting the mass of the spring, Ол:
(a) the law of motion $y(t)$, энд $y$ is the displacement of the body from the equilibrium position;
(b) the maximum and minimum tensions of the spring in the process of motion.
4.37. А particle of mass $m$ moves due to the force $\mathbf{F}=-\alpha m \mathbf{r}$, энд $\alpha$ is a positive тогтмолant, $\mathbf{r}$ is the radius vector of the particle relative to the origin of coordinates. Find the trajectory of its motion if at the initial moment $\mathbf{r}=r_{0} \mathbf{i}$ and the velocity $\mathbf{v}=v_{0} \mathbf{j}$, энд $\mathbf{i}$ and $\mathbf{j}$ are the unit vectors of the $x$ and $y$ axes.
4.38. А body of mass $m$ is suspended from a spring fixed to the ceiling of an elevator car. The stiffness of the spring is $\varkappa$. At the moment $t=0$ the car starts going up with an acceleration $w$. Neglecting the mass of the spring, find the law of motion $y(t)$ of the body relative to the elevator car if $y(0)=0$ and $\dot{y}(0)=0$. Consider the following two cases:
(a) $w=$ тогтмол;
(b) $w=\alpha t$, энд $\alpha$ нь тогтмол.
4.39. А body of mass $m=0.50 \mathrm{~кг}$ is suspended from a rubber cord with elasticity coefficient $k=50 \mathrm{~N} / \mathrm{м}$. Find the maximum distance over which the body can be pulled down for the body's oscillations to remain harmonic. What is the energy of oscillation in this case?
4.40. А body of mass $m$ fell from a height $ц$ onto the pan of a spring balance (Зур. 4.10). The masses of the pan and the spring are negligible, the stiffness of the latter is $x$. Having stuck to the pan, the body starts performing harmonic oscillations in the vertical direction. Find the amplitude and the energy of these oscillations.

